General Manager/Editor-in-Chief and former president, Nigerian Guild of Editors, Mr Gbenga Adefaye, has been appointed as the Provost of the Nigerian Institute of Journalism, Ogba, Ikeja. Chairman, Governing Council of NIJ, Chief Olusegun Osoba, said Adefaye would serve as Provost of the institute with effect from September 1, 2020. Osoba made this known in a letter addressed to Adefaye and obtained by our correspondent on Monday. In the letter dated August 26, Osoba urged the new provost to consider his appointment as a “call to service”. READ ALSO: LASU students to resume in batches – VC Part of the letter read, “I am pleased to inform you that the Governing Council of NIJ at its meeting on August 26 unanimously resolved to appoint you the provost of the institute. “This appointment is effective from September 1, 2020, and will last until a new provost is appointed. “We see this as a call to service on your part to our noble profession, which you served for many years as President of Guild of Editors. “We are looking to your replication of many successes you scored when you steered the affairs of the Guild at its most trying times. Be assured of my full cooperation in the major task ahead of you.” Adefaye succeeds the former NIJ Provost, Mr Gbemiga Ogunleye, who had served out his term meritoriously. Adefaye was a two-term president of the Nigerian Guild of Editors. NIJ is a diploma-awarding monotechnic established in 1963 by the International Press Institute.